[[File:Cath Wallace, 2007.jpg|thumb|Cath Wallace in 2007]]
'''Catherine C. "Cath" Wallace''' (born 1952) is a [[New Zealand]] [[environmentalist]] and academic. She is a lecturer in economics and public policy at [[Victoria University of Wellington]], and has been active in environment organizations in New Zealand. She was awarded the [[Goldman Environmental Prize]] in 1991, for her contributions to the protection of the environment of [[Antarctica]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.goldmanprize.org/node/173  |title=Islands and Island Nations 1991. Cath Wallace. New Zealand |publisher=[[Goldman Environmental Prize]]|accessdate=21 November 2010}}</ref>

